# [[Levered Free Cash Flow (LFCF)]] Definition

> ## Excerpt
> [[Levered Free Cash Flow (LFCF)|Levered free cash flow (LFCF)]] is the money that remains after a company has paid its [[Debt|debt]] obligations and set aside capital for operations.

